text: Châtelus may refer to the following communes in France: * Châtelus, Allier, a commune in the Allier department in the Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes region * Châtelus, Isère, a commune in the Isère department in the Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes region * Châtelus, Loire, a commune in the Loire department in the Auvergne- Rhône-Alpes region * Châtelus-le-Marcheix, a commune in the Creuse department in the Nouvelle-Aquitaine region * Châtelus-Malvaleix, a commune in the Creuse department in the Nouvelle-Aquitaine region
title: Châtelus
